---
import StarlightPage from '@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro';
import CollectionRegister from '@/components/CollectionRegister.astro';
---

<StarlightPage frontmatter={{
  title: 'Guide to the Lorelog',
  description: 'How to read the incident archive without mistaking memory for order.',
  tableOfContents: false,
}}>
  <dl>
    <dt>Status</dt>
    <dd>Semi-coherent, chronically backlogged</dd>
    <dt>Jurisdiction</dt>
    <dd><code>lorelog</code></dd>
  </dl>

  <hr />

  <p>
    The Lorelog is what happens when incident reporting survives long enough to
    become institutional memory and then continues decaying. It does not present
    a clean history. It preserves the archive’s preferred injuries, its repeat
    offenses, and the moments when a failure became important enough to name.
  </p>

  <h2>How to enter</h2>
  <p>
    Read by band, not by completion. A single case file may explain a symptom,
    but a band explains a climate. Case numbers, related entries, and mascot
    references matter more than chronology alone.
  </p>

  <h2>What to look for</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Case number:</strong> where the file lives in the archive’s memory spine.</li>
    <li><strong>Related entries:</strong> where the same failure started rhyming elsewhere.</li>
    <li><strong>Mascot references:</strong> the face a category of wrongness wore in public.</li>
    <li><strong>Doctrine collisions:</strong> places where reference failed to contain behavior.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Recommended band</h2>
  <p>
    Start with the Empathegy band. It is one of the clearest examples of the
    archive measuring a condition and then quietly becoming the condition.
  </p>

  <CollectionRegister
    collection="lorelog"
    filterPrefix="lorelog/llg-08"
    exclude="index"
    sortBy="caseNumber"
  />

  <h2>Nearby shelves</h2>
  <p>
    After a band establishes the injury pattern, pivot into
    <a href="/reference/empathegy">Reference Empathegy</a> to see the official language,
    or into <a href="/mascots">Mascots</a> to see which failure signatures kept recurring.
    If you only stay in Lorelog, the archive starts to look more organized than it is.
  </p>

  <p><a href="/lorelog">Full Lorelog Registry</a></p>
</StarlightPage>
